A photorealistic aerial view of a vast flooded cityscape at dusk, murky brown waters submerging streets and surrounding Victorian-style rooftops, with scattered rescue boats creating gentle ripples across the stillness. In the foreground, a single white egret perches on a partially submerged wrought-iron balcony railing, its pristine feathers contrasting against the destruction. Storm clouds part in the distance revealing a sliver of warm golden light breaking through, casting long reflections across the floodwaters. The mood is somber yet quietly hopeful, emphasizing both devastation and resilience. Shot as if from a helicopter, with rich detail in the waterlogged architecture and debris floating between buildings.
